  <abstract>Illustrated British postcard that depicts a lion with a large mane. In his mane the artist has worked the names of the countries within the British Empire. From top to bottom they read: Canada, India, Australia, New Zealand, African Colonies. The reverse of the postcard reads, "THE MANE IS NOT MERELY A GLORIOUS ORNAMENT BUT A REAL PROTECTION TO A LION" and "A TRIBUTE TO THE COLONIES by William Armitage."</abstract>
